created": 1772568531, "model": "minimax/minimax-m2.5-20260211", "object": "chat.completion.chunk", "service_tier": null, "system_fingerprint": null, "usage": null, "provider": "Parasail"}, {"id": "gen-1772568531-rkRGMFJuAgc6LAmz936x", "choices": [{"delta": {"content": "", "function_call": null, "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "tool_calls": null, "reasoning": "Now I have a good understanding of the project. Let me summarize:\n\n1. **Zac** is a command-line tool that manages a gateway (WebSocket server for agent sessions) and launches a TUI (Terminal User Interface) for real-time interaction with AI agents.\n\n2. **Packages**:\n   - **action-system**: A framework for managing actions, permissions, and execution in a controlled/auditable way\n   - **agent**: An AI agent (likely the Claude agent)\n   - **cli**: Command-line interface\n   - **gateway**: WebSocket server\n   - **tui**: Terminal User Interface\n   - **web**: Web UI served by the gateway\n\nLet me think about helpful additions:\n\n1. **Command history and persistence** - The TUI could save chat history to disk\n2. **More agent commands** - Like `/clear`, `/history`, `/export`\n3. **Better error handling** - More graceful handling of network issues\n4. **Auto-reconnection** - For when the gateway drops\n5. **File transfer** - Ability to send/receive files through the agent\n6. **Multi-session support** - Managing multiple agent sessions\n7. **Better notifications** - Desktop notifications for when agent needs approval\n8. **Voice input/output** - For accessibility\n9. **Plugin system** - Extensibility for custom actions\n10. **Metrics/analytics** - Track usage patterns\n\nLet me look at the current state of the project more to give more specific suggestions.\n"}, "finish_reason": null, "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "native_finish_reason": null}], "created": 1772568531, "model": "minimax/minimax-m2.5-20260211", "object": "chat.completion.chunk", "service_tier": null, "system_fingerprint": null, "usage":